{
  "id": "61e91b392199d5001d1702d6",
  "title": "(4.4.2.2) Read to make a note",
  "created": 1552465395,
  "updated": 1553661628,
  "lines": [
    {
      "id": "61e91b39aff09e000066fc78",
      "text": "(4.4.2.2) Read to make a note",
      "created": 1552465395,
      "updated": 1553661628,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b39aff09e000066fc79",
      "text": "Let's see how to read the selected book.",
      "created": 1552465401,
      "updated": 1552465408,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b39aff09e000066fc7a",
      "text": "",
      "created": 1552465401,
      "updated": 1552465401,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b39aff09e000066fc7b",
      "text": "First of all, [Akinori Takada] insists that you can follow the two principles:",
      "created": 1552465401,
      "updated": 1552465414,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b39aff09e000066fc7c",
      "text": "",
      "created": 1552465401,
      "updated": 1552465401,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b39aff09e000066fc7d",
      "text": "\t[Read when you want to read]",
      "created": 1552465401,
      "updated": 1552465419,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b39aff09e000066fc7e",
      "text": "\t[Read from where you want to read]",
      "created": 1552465401,
      "updated": 1552465824,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b39aff09e000066fc7f",
      "text": "",
      "created": 1552465401,
      "updated": 1552465401,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b39aff09e000066fc80",
      "text": "Those principles are related to [(1.3.1) Learn from what you want to know]. I explain the method of reading mathematical books later. Interestingly, the second principle contradicts the method for mathematical books. [Compare] them later.",
      "created": 1552465827,
      "updated": 1553660179,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b39aff09e000066fc81",
      "text": "",
      "created": 1552465401,
      "updated": 1552465401,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b39aff09e000066fc82",
      "text": "Next, you prepare a note. You decide the whole amount first, for example, 10 pages per chapter, and you write chapter titles in the note. This activity is related to focusing on headings described in [(4.3.3) Attention to headlines] In this case, you hand-copy them rather than pay attention to them. Doing hand-copy is related to [Shakyo] activity described in [(1.3.4.1) Shakyo].",
      "created": 1552465401,
      "updated": 1553661597,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b39aff09e000066fc83",
      "text": "",
      "created": 1552465401,
      "updated": 1552465401,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b39aff09e000066fc84",
      "text": "While reading through the book, you fill the note. There are tips as follows:",
      "created": 1552465401,
      "updated": 1552465630,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b39aff09e000066fc85",
      "text": "",
      "created": 1552465401,
      "updated": 1552465401,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b39aff09e000066fc86",
      "text": " [Record anything you do not understand].",
      "created": 1552465401,
      "updated": 1552465702,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b39aff09e000066fc87",
      "text": " [Record words that appear many times].",
      "created": 1552465401,
      "updated": 1552465708,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b39aff09e000066fc88",
      "text": " [Connect related concepts with lines].",
      "created": 1552465401,
      "updated": 1552465708,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b39aff09e000066fc89",
      "text": " [Connect reasons and conclusions with arrows].",
      "created": 1552465401,
      "updated": 1552465709,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b39aff09e000066fc8a",
      "text": "",
      "created": 1552465401,
      "updated": 1552465401,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b39aff09e000066fc8b",
      "text": "[Comparing] this with the [Whole Mind System]:",
      "created": 1552465401,
      "updated": 1552465643,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b39aff09e000066fc8c",
      "text": "",
      "created": 1552465401,
      "updated": 1552465401,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b39aff09e000066fc8d",
      "text": " \"Record anything you do not understand\" corresponds to \"[❹ Make questions],\"",
      "created": 1552465401,
      "updated": 1552465692,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b39aff09e000066fc8e",
      "text": " \"Recording a word that appears many times\" corresponds to \"[find the keywords]\" in [❷ Preview].",
      "created": 1552465401,
      "updated": 1552465762,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b39aff09e000066fc8f",
      "text": "",
      "created": 1552465401,
      "updated": 1552465401,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b39aff09e000066fc90",
      "text": "Connecting concepts is related to the [KJ method] in chapter 5.",
      "created": 1552465401,
      "updated": 1552465776,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b39aff09e000066fc91",
      "text": "",
      "created": 1552465401,
      "updated": 1552465401,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b39aff09e000066fc92",
      "text": "Footnote:",
      "created": 1552465959,
      "updated": 1552465961,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b39aff09e000066fc93",
      "text": "",
      "created": 1552465963,
      "updated": 1552465963,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b39aff09e000066fc94",
      "text": "\t[Akinori Takada] recommends using a [pencil] to make it erasable. I think you should use your favorite stationery. However, inferior stationery that cannot connect a line may harm your intelligence.",
      "created": 1552465401,
      "updated": 1552466578,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b39aff09e000066fc95",
      "text": "",
      "created": 1552466146,
      "updated": 1552466146,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    },
    {
      "id": "61e91b39aff09e000066fc96",
      "text": "[en.icon]",
      "created": 1553661628,
      "updated": 1553661628,
      "userId": "582e63d27c56960011aff09e"
    }
  ]
}